## Section 9 — Quality control checklist

Run this before every upload. Takes 3 minutes.

### Technical checks
- [ ] Video is exactly 1080×1920 (9:16) — verify in file properties
- [ ] Duration is 45–60 seconds — not under 40s or over 65s
- [ ] Audio is clear, no clipping or distortion
- [ ] Background music is at 10–15% — voice always dominates
- [ ] Subtitles are visible and don't cover TikTok UI (bottom 20% of screen)
- [ ] No watermarks, no logos, no copyright-protected music
- [ ] File size under 500MB (usually 30–80MB for a 60s video at these settings)

### Content checks
- [ ] Hook lands in the first 2 seconds — test by watching with sound off
- [ ] Pacing feels right — not too fast, not too slow
- [ ] Each scene transition is smooth (no jarring cuts)
- [ ] The emotional payoff hits — watch the last 10 seconds fresh
- [ ] Visual style is consistent across all 6 scenes
- [ ] No scene is longer than 12 seconds without movement

### TikTok-specific checks
- [ ] Caption is ready (hook line + 3–4 hashtags, under 150 chars)
- [ ] First 3 seconds would stop a scroll — watch it cold, decide in 3s
- [ ] Sound on + sound off both tell the story (subtitles carry the audio-off experience)
- [ ] No misleading claims, no graphic content

### If something fails the check
- Hook too weak → regenerate 3 alternative hooks with Gemini, swap the first line
- Visual inconsistency → regenerate the outlier scene with the same style prefix
- Subtitle misalignment → re-run Whisper and adjust in the SRT file manually
- Pacing too fast → increase scene duration by 10%, re-export

