### If Gemini free tier limits become a problem

Gemini 2.5 Flash free tier allows 1,500 requests/day. For 1 video/day you use roughly 3–5 requests. You will not hit this limit. If you scale to 10+ videos/day, you may need Gemini paid tier (~$0.15 per million tokens — still well under $5/month at this usage).

### If Pollinations becomes unreliable

Pollinations is free but has occasional rate limiting during peak hours. Solutions:
- Run image generation at off-peak hours (5–7 AM)
- Add retry logic (3 attempts with 30-second delays)
- Keep Ideogram.ai as a backup (100 free images/month)

### Nuclear backup: everything offline

If all cloud APIs disappear (unlikely but worth knowing):
- Stable Diffusion 1.5 runs on 4GB VRAM — install via AUTOMATIC1111
- Piper TTS runs on CPU, zero internet needed
- This gives you a fully local pipeline at zero ongoing cost, with lower quality

